Aim

To load a CSV file using Pandas and perform basic DataFrame operations.

Theory

Pandas is a Python library used for data analysis.
A CSV file stores data in table format.
Using Pandas, we can load, view, and analyze the dataset easily.

Program
import pandas as pd

# Load CSV file
df = pd.read_csv('data.csv')

# Display first rows
print("First Five Rows:")
print(df.head())

# Display shape
print("\nShape of Dataset:")
print(df.shape)

# Display column names
print("\nColumn Names:")
print(df.columns)

# Display dataset information
print("\nDataset Information:")
print(df.info())

# Display statistical summary
print("\nStatistical Summary:")
print(df.describe())

# Check missing values
print("\nMissing Values:")
print(df.isnull().sum())


Procedure
Open Anaconda Navigator.
Launch Jupyter Notebook.
Create a new Python notebook.
Import Pandas library.
Place data.csv in notebook folder.
Use read_csv() to load dataset.
Use head() to display first rows.
Use shape to find rows and columns.
Use info() and describe() for dataset details.
Execute the program and observe output.


